-- FACTBOX: Bombardier's new CSeries jet family
-- 
-- Sun Jul 13, 2008 12:24pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/13/us-airshow-bombardier-factbox-idUSL1334424620080713

 

 (Reuters) - Bombardier ( BBDb.TO ) launched a new 100-145 seat passenger jet, the CSeries, on Sunday in a long-awaited bid by the Canadian company to challenge the dominance of industry giants Airbus ( EAD.PA ) and Boeing ( BA.N ). 

 The five-abreast CSeries family will target a market category estimated by Bombardier at 6,300 aircraft representing more than $250 billion in sales over the next 20 years. Bombardier said it expects to be able to capture up to half of the market. Following are details of the CSeries family: CSeries 110 Seating: configurations range from mixed-class seating for 100 passengers to high-density, single-class seating for 125 passengers Length: 34.8 meters Wingspan: 35.1 meters Range: 4,074 kilometers Engines: Pratt & Whitney ( UTX.N ) Geared Turbofan List price: approximately $46.7 million CSeries 130 Seating: configurations range from mixed-class seating for 120 passengers to high-density, single-class seating for 145 passengers Length: 38.0 meters Wingspan: 35.1 meters Range: 4,074 kilometers Engines: Pratt & Whitney Geared Turbofan List price: approximately $46.7 million (Compiled by James Regan; Editing by Quentin Bryar)